obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2616)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2616&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Geographical`
  line `Indications of Goods (Registration and Protection) Act, 1999.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 15th September, 2003, vide notification No. S.O. 1051(E), dated 15th September, 2003, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2617)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Definitions and interpretation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2617&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(b) authorised user means the authorised user of a geographical indication registered under`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(c) deceptively similar A geographical indication shall be deemed to be deceptively similar to`
  line `another geographical indication if it so nearly resembles that other geographical indication as to be`
  line `likely to deceive or cause confusion;`
  line
  line `(d) district court has the meaning assigned to it in the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908);`
  line
  line `(e) geographical indication, in relation to goods, means an indication which identifies such`
  line `goods as agricultural goods, natural goods or manufactured goods as originating, or manufactured in`
  line `the territory of a country, or a region or locality in that territory, where a given quality, reputation or`
  line `other characteristic of such goods is essentially attributable to its geographical origin and in case`
  line `where such goods are manufactured goods one of the activities of either the production or of`
  line `processing or preparation of the goods concerned takes place in such territory, region or locality, as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, any name which is not the name of a country,`
  line `region or locality of that country shall also be considered as the geographical indication if it relates to`
  line `a specific geographical area and is used upon or in relation to particular goods originating from that`
  line `country, region or locality, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) goods means any agricultural, natural or manufactured goods or any goods of handicraft or`
  line `of industry and includes food stuff;`
  line
  line `(g) indication includes any name, geographical or figurative representation or any combination`
  line `of them conveying or suggesting the geographical origin of goods to which it applies;`
  line
  line `(h) name includes any abbreviation of a name;`
  line
  line `(i) package includes any case, box, container, covering, folder, receptacle, vessel, casket, bottle,`
  line `wrapper, label, band, ticket, reel, frame, capsule, cap, lid, stopper and cork;`
  line
  line `(j) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) producer, in relation to goods, means any person who,--`
  line
  line `(i) if such goods are agricultural goods, produces the goods and includes the person who`
  line `processes or packages such goods;`
  line
  line `(ii) if such goods are natural goods, exploits the goods;`
  line
  line `(iii) if such goods are handicraft or industrial goods, makes or manufactures the goods,`
  line
  line `and includes any person who trades or deals in such production, exploitation, making or manufacturing, as`
  line `the case may be, of the goods;`
  line
  line `(l) register means the Register of Geographical Indications referred to in section 6;`
  line
  line `(m) registered (with its grammatical variations) means registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) registered proprietor, in relation to a geographical indication, means any association of`
  line `persons or of producers or any organisation for the time being entered in the register as proprietor of`
  line `the geographical indication;`
  line
  line `(o) Registrar means the Registrar of Geographical Indications referred to in section 3;`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Trade Marks Act, 1999`
  line `(47 of 1999) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
  line
  line `(3) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, any reference--`
  line
  line `(a) to the use of a geographical indication shall be construed as a reference to the use of a printed`
  line `or other visual representation of the geographical indication;`
  line
  line `(b) to the use of a geographical indication in relation to goods shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the use of the geographical indication upon, or in any physical or in any other relation whatsoever, to`
  line `such goods;`
  line
  line `(c) to a registered geographical indication shall be construed as including a reference to a`
  line `geographical indication registered in the register;`
  line
  line `(d) to the Registrar shall be construed as including a reference to any officer when discharging the`
  line `functions of the Registrar in pursuance of sub-section (2) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) to the Geographical Indications Registry shall be construed as including a reference to any`
  line `office of the Geographical Indications Registry.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (a) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. .Clause (p) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2618)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Registrar of Geographical Indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2618&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller-General of Patents, Designs and`
  line `Trade Marks appointed under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Trade Marks Act, 1999, shall be the`
  line `Registrar of Geographical Indications.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such officers with such designations as it thinks fit for the`
  line `purpose of discharging, under the superintendence and direction of the Registrar, such functions of the`
  line `Registrar under this Act, as he may from time to time authorise them to discharge.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2619)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power of Registrar to withdraw or transfer cases, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2619&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the generality of`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 3, the Registrar may, by order in writing and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded therein, withdraw any matter pending before an officer appointed under the said sub-section (2)`
  line `and deal with such matter himself either de novo or from the stage it was so withdrawn or transfer the same to another officer so appointed who may, subject to special directions in the order of transfer,`
  line `proceed with the matter either de novo or from the stage it was so transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2620)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Geographical Indications Registry and offices thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2620&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of this Act, there`
  line `shall be established a Registry which shall be known as the Geographical Indications Registry.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Geographical Indications Registry shall be at such place as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify, and for the purpose of facilitating the`
  line `registrations of geographical indications, there may be established at such places as the Central`
  line `Government may think fit branch offices of the Geographical Indications Registry.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, define the territorial limits`
  line `within which an office of the Geographical Indications Registry may exercise its functions.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall be a seal of the Geographical Indications Registry.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2621)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Register of Geographical Indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2621&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, a record called the Register`
  line `of geographical indications shall be kept at the head office of the Geographical Indications Registry,`
  line `wherein shall be entered all registered geographical indications with the names, addresses and`
  line `descriptions of the proprietors, the names , addresses and descriptions of authorised users and such other`
  line `matters relating to registered geographical indications as may be prescribed and such registers may be`
  line `maintained wholly or partly on computer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the Registrar to keep`
  line `the records wholly or partly in computer floppies or diskettes or in any other electronic form, subject to`
  line `such safeguards as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where such register is maintained wholly or partly in computer floppies or diskettes or in any`
  line `other electronic form under sub-section (2), any reference in this Act to any entry in the register shall be`
  line `construed as the reference to the entry as maintained on computer floppies or diskettes or in any other`
  line `electronic form, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) No notice of any trust, express or implied or constructive, shall be entered in the register and no`
  line `such notice shall be receivable by the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the superintendence and direction of the Central Government, the register shall be kept`
  line `under the control and management of the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(6) There shall be kept at each branch office of the Geographical Indications Registry a copy of the`
  line `register and such other documents mentioned in section 78 as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2622)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Part A and Part B of the register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2622&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The register referred to in section 6 shall be divided`
  line `into two Parts called respectively Part A and Part B.`
  line
  line `(2) The particulars relating to the registration of the geographical indications shall be incorporated and`
  line `form Part A of the register in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(3) The particulars relating to the registration of the authorised users shall be incorporated and form`
  line `part of Part B of the register in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2623)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Registration to be in respect of particular goods and area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2623&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) A geographical indication may`
  line `be registered in respect of any or all of the goods, comprised in such class of goods as may be classified`
  line `by the Registrar and in respect of a definite territory of a country, or a region or locality in that territory,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall classify the goods under sub-section (1), as far as may be, in accordance with`
  line `the International classification of goods for the purposes of registration of geographical indications.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar may publish in the prescribed manner an alphabetical index of classification of`
  line `goods referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Any question arising as to the class within which any goods fall or the definite area as referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) in respect of which the geographical indication is to be registered or where any goods are not specified in the alphabetical index of goods published under sub-section (3) shall be determined by`
  line `the Registrar whose decision in the matter shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2624)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Prohibition of registration of certain geographical indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2624&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `A geographical indication--`
  line
  line `(a) the use of which would be likely to deceive or cause confusion; or`
  line
  line `(b) the use of which would be contrary to any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(c) which comprises or contains scandalous or obscene matter; or`
  line
  line `(d) which comprises or contains any matter likely to hurt the religious susceptibilities of any class`
  line `or section of the citizens of India; or`
  line
  line `(e) which would otherwise be disentitled to protection in a court; or`
  line
  line `(f) which are determined to be generic names or indications of goods and are, therefore, not or`
  line `ceased to be protected in their country of origin, or which have fallen into disuse in that country; or`
  line
  line `(g) which, although literally true as to the territory, region or locality in which the goods`
  line `originate, but falsely represent to the persons that the goods originate in another territory, region or`
  line `locality, as the case may be,`
  line
  line `shall not be registered as a geographical indication.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this section, "generic names or indications", in relation to goods,`
  line `means the name of a goods which, although relates to the place or the region where the goods was`
  line `originally produced or manufactured, has lost its original meaning and has become the common name of`
  line `such goods and serves as a designation for or indication of the kind, nature, type or other property or`
  line `characteristic of the goods.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--In determining whether the name has become generic, account shall be taken of all`
  line `factors including the existing situation in the region or place in which the name originates and the area of`
  line `consumption of the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2625)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Registration of homonymous geographical indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2625&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 7,`
  line `a homonymous geographical indication may be registered under this Act, if the Registrar is satisfied, after`
  line `considering the practical conditions under which the homonymous indication in question shall be`
  line `differentiated from other homonymous indications and the need to ensure equitable treatment of the`
  line `producers of the goods concerned, that the consumers of such goods shall not be confused or misled in`
  line `consequence of such registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (2626)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Application for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2626&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any association of persons or producers or any organisation`
  line `or authority established by or under any law for the time being in force representing the interest of the`
  line `producers of the concerned goods, who are desirous of registering a geographical indication in relation to`
  line `such goods shall apply in writing to the Registrar in such form and in such manner and accompanied by`
  line `such fees as may be prescribed for the registration of the geographical indication.`
  line
  line `(2) The application under sub-section (1) shall contain--`
  line
  line `(a) a statement as to how the geographical indication serves to designate the goods as originating`
  line `from the concerned territory of the country or region or locality in the country, as the case may be, in`
  line `respect of specific quality, reputation or other characteristics of which are due exclusively or`
  line `essentially to the geographical environment, with its inherent natural and human factors, and the`
  line `production, processing or preparation of which takes place in such territory, region or locality, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) the class of goods to which the geographical indication shall apply;`
  line
  line `(c) the geographical map of the territory of the country or region or locality in the country in`
  line `which the goods orginate or are being manufactured;`
  line
  line `(d) the particulars regarding the appearance of the geographical indication as to whether it is`
  line `comprised of the words or figurative elements or both;`
  line
  line `(e) a statement containing such particulars of the producers of the concerned goods, if any,`
  line `proposed to be initially registered with the registration of the geographical indication as may be`
  line `prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) A single application may be made for registration of a geographical indication for different classes`
  line `of goods and fee payable therefor shall be in respect of each such class of goods.`
  line
  line `(4) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be filed in the office of the Geographical Indications`
  line `Registry within whose territorial limits, the territory of the country or the region or locality in the country`
  line `to which the geographical indication relates is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such territory, region or locality, as the case may be, is not situated in India, the`
  line `application shall be filed in the office of the Geographical Indications Registry within whose territorial`
  line `limits the place mentioned in the address for services in India as disclosed in the application, is situated.`
  line
  line `(5) Every applications under sub-section (1) shall be examined by the Registrar in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Registrar may refuse the application or may accept it`
  line `absolutely or subject to such amendments, modification, conditions or limitations, if any, as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(7) In the case of refusal or conditional acceptance of application, the Registrar shall record in writing`
  line `the grounds for such refusal or conditional acceptance and the materials used by him in arriving at his`
  line decision.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (2627)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Withdrawal of acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2627&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where, after the acceptance of an application for registration of a`
  line `geographical indication but before its registration, the Registrar is satisfied,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the application has been accepted in error, or`
  line
  line `(b) that in the circumstances of the case the geographical indication should not be registered or`
  line `should be registered subject to conditions or limitations or to conditions additional to or different from`
  line `the conditions or limitations subject to which the application has been accepted,`
  line
  line `the Registrar may, after hearing the applicant if he so desires, withdraw the acceptance and proceed as if`
  line `the application had not been accepted.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (2628)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Advertisement of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2628&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an application for registration of a geographical`
  line `indication has been accepted, whether absolutely or subject to conditions or limitations, the Registrar`
  line `shall, as soon as may be after acceptance, cause the application as accepted together with the conditions or`
  line `limitations, if any, subject to which it has been accepted, to be advertised in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) Where after advertisement of an application--`
  line
  line `(a) an error in the application has been corrected; or`
  line
  line `(b) the application has been permitted to be amended under section 15,`
  line `the Registrar may, in his discretion cause the application to be advertised again or instead of causing the`
  line `application to be advertised again, notify in the prescribed manner, the correction made in the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (2629)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Opposition to registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2629&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person may, within three months from the date of`
  line `advertisement or readvertisement of an application for registration or within such further period, not`
  line `exceeding one month, in the aggregate, as the Registrar, on application made to him in such manner and`
  line `on payment of such fee as may be prescribed allows, give notice in writing in the prescribed manner to the`
  line `Registrar, of opposition to the registration.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall serve a copy of the notice on the applicant for registration and, within two`
  line `months from the receipt by the applicant of such copy of the notice of opposition, the applicant shall sent to the Registrar in the prescribed manner a counter-statement of the grounds on which he relies for his`
  line `application, and if he does not do so, he shall be deemed to have abandoned his application.`
  line
  line `(3) If the applicant sends such counter-statement, the Registrar shall serve a copy thereof on the`
  line `person giving notice of opposition.`
  line
  line `(4) Any evidence upon which the opponent and the applicant may rely shall be submitted in such`
  line `manner and within the such time as may be prescribed to the Registrar, and the Registrar shall give an`
  line `opportunity to them to be heard, if they so desire.`
  line
  line `(5) The Registrar shall, after hearing the parties, if so required, and considering the evidence, decide`
  line `whether and subject to what conditions or limitations, if any, the registration is to be permitted, and may`
  line `take into account a ground of objection whether relied upon by the opponent or not.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a person giving notice of opposition or an applicant sending a counter-statement after`
  line `receipt of a copy of such notice neither resides nor carries on business in India, the Registrar may require`
  line `him to give security for the costs of proceeding before him, and in default of such security being duly`
  line `given, may treat the opposition or application, as the case may be, as abandoned.`
  line
  line `(7) The Registrar may, on request, permit correction of any error in, or any amendment of, a notice of`
  line `opposition or a counter-statement on such terms as he thinks just.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (2630)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Correction and amendment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2630&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may, on such terms, as he thinks just, at any time,`
  line `whether before or after acceptance of an application for registration under section 11, permit the`
  line `correction of any error or in connection with the application or permit an amendment of the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an amendment is made to a single application referred to in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 11 involving division of such application into two or more applications, the date of making of the`
  line `initial application shall be deemed to be the date of making of the divided applications so divided.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (2631)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2631&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 12, when an application for registration of`
  line `a geographical indication has been accepted and either--`
  line
  line `(a) the application has not been opposed and the time for notice of opposition has expired; or`
  line
  line `(b) the application has been opposed and the opposition has been decided in favour of the`
  line applicant,
  line
  line `the Registrar shall, unless the Central Government otherwise directs, register the said geographical`
  line `indication and the authorised users, if any, mentioned in the application and the geographical indication`
  line `and the authorised users when registered shall be registered as of the date of the making of the said`
  line `application and that date shall, subject to the provisions of section 84, be deemed to be the date of`
  line registration.
  line
  line `(2) On the registration of a geographical indication, the Registrar shall issue each to the applicant and`
  line `the authorised users, if registered with the geographical indication, a certificate in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed of the registration thereof, sealed with the seal of the Geographical Indications Registry.`
  line
  line `(3) Where registration of a geographical indication is not completed within twelve months from the`
  line `date of the application by reason of default on the part of the applicant, the Registrar may, after giving`
  line `notice to the applicant in the prescribed manner, treat the application as abandoned unless it is completed`
  line `within the time specified in that behalf in the notice.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar may amend the register or a certificate of registration for the purpose of correcting a`
  line `clerical error or an obvious mistake.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (2632)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Application for registration as authorised user.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2632&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person claiming to be the producer`
  line `of the goods in respect of which a geographical indication has been registered under section 16 may apply`
  line `in writing to the Registrar in the prescribed manner for registering him as an authorised user of such`
  line `geographical indication.`
  line
  line `(2) The application under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by a statement and such documents of`
  line `facts as may be prescribed and required by the Registrar to determine as to whether such person is the`
  line `producer of the goods referred to in that sub-section and such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Chapter relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) the filing and examination of the application;`
  line
  line `(b) the refusal and acceptance of registration;`
  line
  line `(c) withdrawal of acceptance of application;`
  line
  line `(d) advertisement of application;`
  line
  line `(e) opposition to registration;`
  line
  line `(f) correction or error in an amendment of the application; and`
  line
  line `(g) registration,`
  line
  line `shall apply in respect of the application and registration of authorised users referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `in the same manner as they apply for the application for registration and registration of the geographical`
  line indication.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (2633)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Duration, renewal, removal and restoration of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2633&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registration of a`
  line `geographical indication shall be for a period of ten years, but may be renewed from time to time in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The registration of an authorised user shall be for a period of ten years or for the period till the date`
  line `on which the registration of the geographical indication in respect of which the authorised user is`
  line `registered expires, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall, on application made in the prescribed manner, by the registered proprietor or`
  line `by the authorised user and within the prescribed period and subject to the payment of the prescribed fee,`
  line `renew the registration of the geographical indication or authorised user, as the case may be, for a period of`
  line `ten years from the date of expiration of the original registration or of the last renewal of registration, as`
  line `the case may be (which date is in this section referred to as the expiration of the last registration).`
  line
  line `(4) At the prescribed time before the expiration of the last registration of a geographical indication or`
  line `the authorised user, as the case may be, the Registrar shall send notice in the prescribed manner to the`
  line `registered proprietor or the authorised user, as the case may be, of the date of expiration and the`
  line `conditions as to payment of fees and otherwise upon which a renewal of registration may be obtained,`
  line `and, if at the expiration of time prescribed in that behalf those conditions have not been duly complied`
  line `with, the Registrar may remove the geographical indication or the authorised user, as the case may be,`
  line `from the register:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar shall not remove the geographical indication or the authorised user, as the`
  line `case may be, from the register, if an application is made in the prescribed form and the prescribed fee and`
  line `surcharge is paid within six months from the expiration of the last registration of the geographical`
  line `indication or the authorised user, as the case may be, and shall renew the registration of geographical`
  line `indication or the authorised user, as the case may be, for a period of ten years under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) Where a geographical indication or authorised user, as the case may be, has been removed from the`
  line `register for non-payment of the prescribed fee, the Registrar shall, after six months and within one year`
  line `from the expiration of the last registration of the geographical indication or the authorised user, as the case`
  line `may be, on receipt of an application in the prescribed form and on payment of the prescribed fee, if`
  line `satisfied that it is just so to do, restore the geographical indication or the authorised user, as the case may`
  line `be, to the register and renew registration of the geographical indication or authorised user, as the case may`
  line `be, either generally or subject to such condition or limitation as he thinks fit to impose, for a period of ten`
  line `years from the expiration of the last registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (2634)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Effect of removal from register for failure to pay fee for renewal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22, for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2634&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where a geographical`
  line `indication has been removed from the register for failure to pay the fee for renewal, it shall nevertheless,`
  line `for the purpose of any application for the registration of another geographical indication during one year, next after the date of removal, be deemed to be a geographical indication already on the register, unless`
  line `the ^1[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] is satisfied either--`
  line
  line `(a) that there has been no bona fide trade use of the geographical indication which has been`
  line `removed within the two years immediately preceding its removal; or`
  line
  line `(b) that no deception or confusion would be likely to arise from the use of the geographical`
  line `indication which is the subject of the application for registration by reason of any previous use of the`
  line `geographical indication which has been removed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (2635)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `No action for infringement of unregistered geographical indication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2635&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be`
  line `entitled to institute any proceeding to prevent, or to recover damages for, the infringement of an`
  line `unregistered geographical indication.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to affect rights of action against any person for passing off`
  line `goods as the goods of another person or the remedies in respect thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (2636)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Rights conferred by registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2636&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the`
  line `registration of a geographical indication shall, if valid, give,--`
  line
  line `(a) to the registered proprietor of the geographical indication and the authorised user or users`
  line `thereof the right to obtain relief in respect of infringement of the geographical indication in the`
  line `manner provided by this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to the authorised user thereof the exclusive right to the use of the geographical indication in`
  line `relation to the goods in respect of which the geographical indication is registered.`
  line
  line `(2) The exclusive right to the use of a geographical indication given under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be subject to any condition and limitation to which the registration is subject.`
  line
  line `(3) Where two or more persons are authorised users of geographical indications, which are identical`
  line `with or nearly resemble each other, the exclusive right to the use of any of those geographical indications`
  line `shall not (except so far as their respective rights are subject to any conditions or limitations entered on the`
  line `register) be deemed to have been acquired by anyone of those persons as against any other of those`
  line `persons merely by registration of the geographical indications, but each of those persons has otherwise the`
  line `same rights as against other persons as he would have if he were the sole authorised user.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (2637)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Infringement or registered geographical indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2637&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered geographical indication`
  line `is infringed by a person who, not being an authorised user thereof,--`
  line
  line `(a) uses such geographical indication by any means in the designations or presentation of goods`
  line `that indicates or suggests that such goods originate in a geographical area other than the true place of`
  line `origin of such goods in a manner which misleads the persons as to the geographical origin of such`
  line `goods; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses any geographical indication in such manner which constitutes an act of unfair`
  line `competition including passing off in respect of registered geographical indication.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this clause, act of unfair competition means any act of`
  line `competition contrary to honest practices in industrial or commercial matters.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the following acts shall be`
  line `deemed to be acts of unfair competition, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) all acts of such a nature as to create confusion by any means whatsoever with the`
  line `establishment, the goods or the industrial or commercial activities, of a competitor;`
  line
  line `(ii) false allegations in the course of trade of such a nature as to discredit the establishment,`
  line `the goods or the industrial or commercial activities, of a competitor;`
  line
  line `(iii) geographical indications, the use of which in the course of trade is liable to mislead the`
  line `persons as to the nature, the manufacturing process, the characteristics, the suitability for their`
  line `purpose, or the quantity, of the goods;`
  line
  line `(c) uses another geographical indication to the goods which, although literally true as to the`
  line `territory, region or locality in which the goods originate, falsely represents to the persons that the`
  line `goods originate in the territory, region or locality in respect of which such registered geographical`
  line `indication relates.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, if it thinks necessary so to do for providing additional protection to`
  line `certain goods or classes of goods under sub-section (3), by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `such goods or class or classes of goods, for the purposes of such protection.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who is not an authorised user of a geographical indication registered under this Act in`
  line `respect of the goods or any class or classes of goods notified under sub-section (2), uses any other`
  line `geographical indication to such goods or class or classes of goods not originating in the place indicated by`
  line `such other geographical indication or uses such other geographical indication to such goods or class or`
  line `classes of goods even indicating the true origin of such goods or uses such other geographical indication`
  line `to such goods or class or classes of goods in translation of the true place of origin or accompanied by`
  line `expression such as 'kind", "style", imitation or the like expression, shall infringe such registered`
  line `geographical indication.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where the goods in respect of which a`
  line `geographical indication has been registered are lawfully acquired by a person other than the authorised`
  line `user of such geographical indication, further dealings in those goods by such person including processing`
  line `or packaging, shall not constitute an infringement of such geographical indication, except where the`
  line `condition of goods is impaired after they have been put in the market.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (2638)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Registration to be prima facie evidence of validity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22, for "and before the Appellate Board" (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2638&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all legal proceedings relating to a`
  line `geographical indication, the certificate of registration granted in this regard by the Registrar under this`
  line `Act, being a copy of the entry in the register under the seal of the Geographical Indications Registry, shall`
  line `be prima facie evidence of the validity thereof and be admissible in all courts and ^1[before whom] without further proof or production of the original.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to be affect the right of action in respect of an unregistered`
  line `geographical indication.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (2639)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Prohibition of assignment or transmission, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2639&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, any right to a registered geographical indication shall not be the subject`
  line `matter of assignment, transmission, licensing, pledge, mortgage or any such other agreement:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the death of an authorised user his right in a registered geographical indication shall`
  line `devolve on his successor in title under the law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (2640)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Prohibition of registration of geographical indication as trade mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2640&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of 1999), the Registrar of Trade Marks referred to in`
  line `section 3 of that Act, shall, suo motu or at the request of an interested party, refuse or invalidate the`
  line `registration of a trade mark which--`
  line
  line `(a) contains or consists of a geographical indication with respect to the goods or class or classes`
  line `of goods not originating in the territory of a country, or a region or locality in that territory which such`
  line `geographical indication indicates, if use of such geographical indications in the trade mark for such`
  line `goods, is of such a nature as to confuse or mislead the persons as to the true place of origin of such`
  line `goods or class or classes of goods;`
  line
  line `(b) contains or consists of a geographical indication identifying goods or class or classes of goods`
  line `notified under sub-section (2) of section 22.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (2641)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Protection to certain trade marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2641&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a trade mark contains or consists of a`
  line `geographical indication and has been applied for or registered in good faith under the law relating to trade marks for the time being in force, or where rights to such trade mark have been acquired through use in`
  line `good faith either--`
  line
  line `(a) before the commencement of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) before the date of filing the application for registration of such geographical indication under`
  line `this Act,`
  line
  line `nothing contained in this Act shall prejudice the registrability or the validity of the registration of such`
  line `trade mark under the law relating to the trade marks for the time being in force, or the right to use such`
  line `trade mark, on the ground that such trade mark is identical with or similar to such geographical indication.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this Act shall apply in respect of a geographical indication with respect to`
  line `goods or class or classes of goods for which such geographical indication is identical with the term`
  line `customary in common language as the common name of such goods in any part of India on or before the`
  line `1st day of January, 1995.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this Act shall in any way prejudice the right of any person to use, in the`
  line `course of trade, that person's name or the name of that person's predecessor in business, except where`
  line `such name is used in such a manner as to confuse or mislead the people.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of 1999) or in this Act, no`
  line `action in connection with the use or registration of a trade mark shall be taken after the expiry of five`
  line `years from the date on which such use or registration infringes any geographical indication registered`
  line `under this Act has become known to the registered proprietor or authorised user registered in respect of`
  line `such geographical indication under this Act or after the date of registration of the trade mark under the`
  line `said Trade Marks Act subject to the condition that the trade mark has been published under the provisions`
  line `of the said Trade Marks Act, 1999 or the rules made thereunder by that date, if such date is earlier than the`
  line `date on which such infringement became known to such proprietor or authorised user and such`
  line `geographical indication is not used or registered in bad faith.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (2642)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to cancel or vary registration and to rectify the register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2642&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) On application made in`
  line `the prescribed manner to the ^1[High Court] or to the Registrar by any person aggrieved, the ^2[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,]`
  line `may make such order as it may think fit for cancelling or varying the registration of a geographical`
  line `indication or authorised user on the ground of any contravention, or failure to observe the condition`
  line `entered on the register in relation thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by the absence or omission from the register of any entry, or by any entry`
  line `made in the register without sufficient cause, or by any entry wrongly remaining on the register, or by any`
  line `error or defect in any entry in the register, may apply in the prescribed manner to the ^1[High Court] or`
  line `to the Registrar, and the ^2[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] may make such order for making, expunging or varying the entry as it`
  line `may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^2[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] may in any proceeding under this section decide any question that may be necessary`
  line `or expedient to decide in connection with the rectification of the register.`
  line
  line `(4) The ^2[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,], of its own motion, may, after giving notice in the prescribed manner to the parties`
  line `concerned and after giving them an opportunity of being heard, make any order referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1) or sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) Any order of the ^1[High Court] rectifying the register shall direct that notice of the rectification`
  line `shall be served upon the Registrar in the prescribed manner who shall upon receipt of such notice rectify`
  line `the register accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 22. ibid., for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (2643)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Correction of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2643&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may, on application made in the prescribed manner by`
  line `the registered proprietor or the authorised user,--`
  line
  line `(a) correct any error in the name, address or description of the registered proprietor or the`
  line `authorised user, as the case may be, of a geographical indication, or any other entry relating to the`
  line `geographical indication on the register;`
  line
  line `(b) enter any change in the name, address or description of the association of persons or of`
  line `producers or any ogranisation or authority, as the case may be, who is registered as proprietor of a`
  line `geographical indication on the register;`
  line
  line `(c) cancel the entry of a geographical indication on the register;`
  line
  line `(d) strike out any goods or class or classes of goods from those in respect of which a geographical`
  line `indication is registered from the register,`
  line
  line `and may make any consequential amendment or alteration in the certificate of registration, and for that`
  line `purpose, may require the certificate of registration to be produced to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (2644)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Alteration of registered geographical indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2644&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registered proprietor of a`
  line `geographical indication may apply in the prescribed manner to the Registrar for leave to add to or alter the`
  line `geographical indication in any manner not substantially affecting the identity thereof, and the Registrar`
  line `may refuse leave or may grant it on such terms and subject to such limitations as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may cause an application under this section to be advertised in the prescribed`
  line `manner in any case where it appears to him that it is expedient so to do, and where he does so, if within`
  line `the prescribed time from the date of the advertisement any person gives notice to the Registrar in the`
  line `prescribed manner of the opposition to the application, the Registrar shall, after hearing the parties if so`
  line `required, decide the matter.`
  line
  line `(3) Where leave is granted under this section, the geographical indication as altered shall be`
  line `advertised in the prescribed manner, unless the application has already been advertised under`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (2645)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Adaptation of entries in register to amend or substitute classification of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2645&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Registrar shall not make any amendment of the register which would have the effect of adding any goods`
  line `or classes of goods to those in respect of which a geographical indication is registered (whether in one or`
  line `more classes) immediately before the amendment is to be made or antedating the registration of a`
  line `geographical indication in respect of any goods:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section, shall not apply when the Registrar is satisfied that compliance`
  line `therewith would involve complexity and that the addition or antedating, as the case may be, would not`
  line `affect any substantial quantity of goods and would not substantially prejudice the rights of any person.`
  line
  line `(2) A proposal so to amend the register shall be brought to the notice of the registered proprietor and`
  line `every authorised user of the geographical indication affected and advertised in the prescribed manner, and`
  line `may be opposed before the Registrar by any person aggrieved on the ground that the proposed amendment`
  line `contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (2646)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Appeals to the High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2646&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order or decision of the`
  line `Registrar under this Act, or the rules made thereunder, may prefer an appeal to the ^1[High Court] within`
  line `three months from the date on which the order or decision sought to be appealed against is communicated`
  line
  line `to such person preferring the appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of the period specified under`
  line `sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period specified therefore, if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the ^1[High Court] that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the`
  line `specified period.`
  line
  line ^2*****
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2.Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (2647)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of courts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2647&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Omitted by The Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021 (33 of 2021), s.`
  line `22 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (2648)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Procedure of the Appellate Board.`
  content `Omitted by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2648&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (2649)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Procedure for application for rectification, etc., before High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2649&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application`
  line `for rectification of the register made to the ^1[High Court] under section 27 shall be in such form as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A certified copy of every order or judgment of the ^1[High Court] relating to a registered`
  line `geographical indication under this Act shall be communicated to the Registrar by the ^1[High Court] and`
  line `the Registrar shall give effect to the order of the Board and shall, when so directed, amend the entries in,`
  line `or rectify, the register in accordance with such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (2650)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Appearance of Registrar in legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2650&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar shall have the right to appear`
  line `and be heard--`
  line
  line `(a) in any legal proceedings before the ^1[High Court] in which the relief sought includes`
  line `alteration or rectification of the register or in which any question relating to the practice of the`
  line `Geographical Indications Registry is raised;`
  line
  line `(b) in any appeal to the Board from an order of the Registrar on an application for registration of a`
  line `geographical indication or authorised user--`
  line
  line `(i) which is not opposed, and the application is either refused by the Registrar or is accepted`
  line `by him subject to any amendments, modifications, conditions or limitations, or`
  line
  line `(ii) which has been opposed and the Registrar considers that his appearance is necessary in`
  line `the public interest,`
  line
  line `and the Registrar shall appear in any case if so directed by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless the ^1[High Court] otherwise directs, the Registrar may, in lieu of appearing, submit a`
  line `statement in writing signed by him, giving such particulars as he thinks proper of the proceedings before`
  line `him relating to the matter in issue or of the grounds of any decision given by him affecting it, or of the`
  line `practice of the Geographical Indications Registry in like cases, or of other matters relevant to the issues`
  line `and within his knowledge as Registrar, and such statement shall be evidence in the proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (2651)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Costs of Registrar in proceedings before Appellate Board.`
  content `Omitted by The Tribunal Reforms Act 2021 (33 of 2021), s. 22 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2651&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (2652)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Meaning of applying geographical indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2652&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be deemed to apply a`
  line `geographical indication to goods who--`
  line
  line `(a) applies it to the goods themselves; or`
  line
  line `(b) applies it to any package in or with which the goods are sold, or exposed for sale, or had in`
  line `possession for sale or for any purpose of trade or manufacture; or`
  line
  line `(c) places, encloses or annexes any goods which are sold, or exposed for sale, or had in`
  line `possession for sale or for any purpose of trade or manufacture, in or with any package or other thing`
  line `to which a geographical indication has been applied; or`
  line
  line `(d) uses a geographical indication in any manner reasonably likely to lead to the belief that the`
  line `goods in connection with which it is used are designated or described by that geographical indication;`
  line or
  line
  line `(e) in relation to the goods uses a geographical indication in any sign, advertisement, invoice,`
  line `catalogue, business letter, business paper, price list or other commercial documents and goods are`
  line `delivered to a person in pursuance of a request or order made by reference to the geographical`
  line `indication as so used.`
  line
  line `(2) A geographical indication shall be deemed to be applied to goods whether it is woven in,`
  line `impressed on, or otherwise worked into, or annexed or affixed to, the goods or to any package or other`
  line thing.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37_a:
  sectionId (93230)
  sectionNo 37A
  orderNo 38
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=93230&sectionno=37A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[37A. Adjudication of penalties.— The Registrar may, by an order, authorise an officer referred to`
  line `in section 3, to be adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry and imposing penalty under the provisions of`
  line `this Act, in the manner as may be prescribed, after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_b:
  sectionId (93231)
  sectionNo 37B
  orderNo 39
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=93231&sectionno=37B&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_37_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[37B. Appeal.—(1) Whoever aggrieved by an order of the adjudicating officer under section 37A may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the appellate authority, who shall be an officer at least one rank above the adjudicating`
  line `officer, within a period of sixty days from the date of receipt of the order, as the Central Government may`
  line `by notification authorise in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period of sixty days if the appellant satisfies the`
  line `appellate authority that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) No appeal shall be disposed of unless the appellant has been given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) The appellate authority referred to in sub-section (1) shall dispose of the appeal within sixty days`
  line `from the date of filing.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if the person fails to comply with the order of the`
  line `adjudicating officer under section 37A or the order of the appellate authority under this section, as the`
  line `case may be, within ninety days of such order, he shall, in addition to the penalty, be punishable with fine`
  line `of one lakh rupees or imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (2653)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Falsifying and falsely applying geographical indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2653&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be deemed to`
  line `falsify a geographical indication who, either,--`
  line
  line `(a) without the assent of the authorised user of the geographical indication makes that`
  line `geographical indication or deceptively similar geographical indication; or`
  line
  line `(b) falsifies any genuine geographical indication, whether by alteration, addition, effacement or`
  line otherwise.
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be deemed to falsely apply to goods a geographical indication who, without the`
  line `assent of the authorised user of the geographical indication,--`
  line
  line `(a) applies such geographical indication or a deceptively similar geographical indication to goods`
  line `or any package containing goods;`
  line
  line `(b) uses any package bearing a geographical indication which is identical with or deceptively`
  line `similar to the geographical indication of such authorised user, for the purpose of packing, filling or`
  line `wrapping therein any goods other than the genuine goods of the authorised user of the geographical`
  line indication.
  line
  line `(3) Any geographical indication falsified as mentioned in sub-section (1) or falsely applied as`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (2), is in this Act referred to as a false geographical indication.`
  line
  line `(4) In any prosecution for falsifying a geographical indication or falsely applying a geographical`
  line `indication to goods, the burden of proving the assent of proprietor shall lie on the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (2654)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Penalty for applying false geographical indications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2654&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) falsifies any geographical indication; or`
  line
  line `(b) falsely applies to goods any geographical indication; or`
  line
  line `(c) makes, disposes of, or has in his possession, any die, block, machine, plate or other instrument`
  line `for the purpose of falsifying or of being used for falsifying, a geographical indication; or`
  line
  line `(d) applies to any goods to which an indication of the country or place in which they were made`
  line `or produced or the name and the address of the manufacturer or person for whom the goods are`
  line `manufactured is required to be applied under section 71, a false indication of such country, place,`
  line `name or address; or`
  line
  line `(e) tampers with, alters or effaces an indication of origin which has been applied to any goods to`
  line `which it is required to be applied under section 71; or`
  line
  line `(f) causes any of the things above-mentioned in this section to be done,`
  line
  line `shall, unless he proves that he acted, without intent to defraud, be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to three years and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than six months or a fine of less than fifty thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (2655)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Penalty for selling goods to which false geographical indication is applied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2655&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Any person who`
  line `sells, lets for hire or exposes for sale, or hires or has in his possession for sale, goods or things to which`
  line `any false geographical indication is applied or which, being required under section 71 to have applied to`
  line `them an indication of the country or place in which they were made or produced or the name and address`
  line `of the manufacturer, or person for whom the goods are manufactured or without the indications so`
  line `required, shall, unless he proves,--`
  line
  line `(a) that, having taken all reasonable precautions against committing an offence against this`
  line `section, he had at the time of commission of the alleged offence no reason to suspect the genuineness`
  line `of the geographical indication or that any offence had been committed in respect of the goods; or`
  line
  line `(b) that, on demand by or on behalf of the prosecutor, he gave all the information in his power`
  line `with respect to the person from whom he obtained such goods or things; or`
  line
  line `(c) that otherwise he had acted innocently,`
  line
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend`
  line `to three years and with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to`
  line `two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than six months or a fine of less than fifty thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (2656)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Enhanced penalty on second or subsequent conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2656&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Whoever having already been`
  line `convicted of an offence under section 39 or section 40 is again convicted of any such offence shall be`
  line `punishable for the second and for every subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which shall not`
  line `be less than one year but which may extend to three years and with fine which shall not be less than one`
  line `lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for adequate and special reason to be mentioned in the judgment, impose`
  line `a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than one year or a fine of less than one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that for the purposes of this section, no cognizance shall be taken of any conviction`
  line `made before the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (2657)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Penalty for falsely representing a geographical indication as registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2657&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall`
  line `make any representation---`
  line
  line `(a) with respect to a geographical indication, not being a registered geographical indication, to the`
  line `effect that it is a registered geographical indication; or`
  line
  line `(b) to the effect that a registered geographical indication is registered in respect of any goods in`
  line `respect of which it is not in fact registered; or`
  line
  line `(c) to the effect that registration of a geographical indication gives an exclusive right to the use`
  line `thereof in any circumstances in which having regard to limitation entered on the register, the`
  line `registration does not in fact give that right.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes any of the provisions of sub-section (1), he shall be ^1[liable to penalty of`
  line `a sum equal to one-half per cent. of the total sales or turnover, as the case may be, in business or of the`
  line `gross receipts in profession as computed in the audited accounts of such person, or a sum equal to five`
  line `lakh rupees, whichever is less ].`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section the use in India in relation to a geographical indication of the`
  line `words "registered geographical indication" or any other expression, symbol or sign like "R.G.I." referring`
  line `whether expressly or impliedly to registration, shall be deemed to import a reference to registration in the`
  line `register, except---`
  line
  line `(a) where that word or other expression, symbol or sign is used in direct association with other`
  line `words delineated in characters at least as large as those in which that word or other expression,`
  line `symbol or sign is delineated and indicating that the reference to registration as a geographical`
  line `indication under the law of a country outside India being a country under the law of which the`
  line `registration referred to is in fact in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) where that other expression, symbol or sign is of itself such as to indicate that the reference is`
  line `to such registration as is mentioned in clause (a); or`
  line
  line `(c) where that word is used in relation to a geographical indication registered under the law of a`
  line `country outside India and in relation solely to goods to be exported to that country for use in that`
  line country.
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (2658)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2658&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `43. [Penalty for improperly describing a place of business as connected with the Geographical`
  line `Indications Registry.]— Omitted by The Jan Vishwas (amendment of Provisions) Act, 2023 (18 of 2023),`
  line `s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (2659)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2659&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `44. [Penalty for falsification of entries in the register.]--- Omitted by The Jan Vishwas (amendment of Provisions) Act, 2023 (18 of 2023),`
  line `s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (2660)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 47
  title `No offence in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2660&sectionno=45&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 39, 40 and 41 shall in relation to a`
  line `registered geographical indication or authorised user of such geographical indication, be subject to the`
  line `rights created or recognised by this Act and no act or omission shall be deemed to be an offence under the`
  line `aforesaid sections if,--`
  line
  line `(a) the alleged offence relates to a registered geographical indication and the act or omission is`
  line `permitted under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) the alleged offence relates to a registered geographical indication and the act or omission is`
  line `permitted under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (2661)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 48
  title `Forfeiture of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2661&sectionno=46&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person is convicted of an offence under section 39 or section`
  line `40 or section 41 or is acquitted of an offence under section 39 or section 40 on proof that he acted without`
  line `intend or defraud, or under section 40 on proof of the matters specified in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause`
  line `(c) of that section, the court convicting or acquitting him may direct the forfeiture to Government of all`
  line `goods and things by means of, or in relation to, which the offence has been committed, or but for such`
  line `proof as aforesaid would have been committed.`
  line
  line `(2) When a forfeiture is directed on a conviction and an appeal lies against the conviction, an appeal`
  line `shall lie against the forfeiture also.`
  line
  line `(3) When, a forfeiture is directed on acquittal and the goods or things to which the direction relates`
  line `are of value exceeding fifty rupees, an appeal against the forfeiture may be preferred, within thirty days`
  line `from the date of the direction, to the court to which in appealable cases appeal lie from sentences of the`
  line `court which directed the forfeiture.`
  line
  line `(4) When a forfeiture is directed on a conviction, the court, before whom the person is convicted, may`
  line `order any forfeited articles to be destroyed or otherwise disposed of as the court thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (2662)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 49
  title `Exemption of certain persons employed in ordinary course of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2662&sectionno=47&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Where a person`
  line `accused of an offence under section 39 proves,--`
  line
  line `(a) that in the ordinary course of his business he is employed on behalf of other persons to apply`
  line `geographical indications, or as the case may be, to make dies, blocks, machines, plates, or other`
  line `instruments for making, or being used in making, geographical indications;`
  line
  line `(b) that in the case which is the subject of the charge he was so employed, and was not interested`
  line `in the goods or other thing by way of profit or commission depend on the sale of such goods;`
  line
  line `(c) that, having taken all reasonable precautions against committing the offence charged, he had,`
  line `at the time of the commission of the alleged offence, no reason to suspect the genuineness of the`
  line `geographical indication; and`
  line
  line `(d) that, on demand made by or on behalf of the prosecutor, he gave all the information in his`
  line `power with respect to the persons on whose behalf the geographical indication was applied,`
  line
  line `he shall be acquitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (2663)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 50
  title `Procedure where invalidity of registration is pleaded by the accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2663&sectionno=48&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the offence`
  line `charged under section 39 or section 40 or section 41 is in relation to a registered geographical indication`
  line `and the accused pleads that the registration of the geographical indication is invalid, the following`
  line `procedure shall be followed:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the court is satisfied that such defence is prima facie tenable, it shall not proceed with the`
  line `charge but shall adjourn the proceeding for three months from the date on which the plea of the`
  line `accused is recorded to enable the accused to file an application before the ^1[High Court] under this`
  line `Act, for the rectification of the register on the ground that the registration is invalid;`
  line
  line `(b) if the accused proves to the court that he has made such application within the time so limited`
  line `or within such further time as the court may for sufficient cause allow, the further proceedings in the`
  line `prosecution shall stand stayed till the disposal of such application for rectification;`
  line
  line `(c) if within a period of three months or within such extended time as may be allowed by the court`
  line `the accused fails to apply to the ^1[High Court] for rectification of the register, the court shall`
  line `proceed with the case as if the registration were valid.`
  line
  line `(2) Where before the institution of a complaint of an offence referred to in sub-section (1), any`
  line `application for the rectification of the register concerning the geographical indication in question on the`
  line `ground of invalidity of the registration thereof has already been properly made to and is pending before`
  line `the ^2[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] the court shall stay the further proceedings in the prosecution pending the disposal of the`
  line `application aforesaid and shall determine the charge against the accused in conformity with the result of`
  line `the application for rectification in so far as the complainant relies upon the registration of his geographical`
  line indication.
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for “tribunal” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (2664)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 51
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2664&sectionno=49&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing an offence under this Act is a company,`
  line `the company as well as every person in charge of, and responsible to, the company for the conduct of its`
  line `business at the time of the commission of the offence shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall`
  line `be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or that the commission of the offence is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (2665)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 52
  title `Cognizance of certain offences and the powers of police officer for search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2665&sectionno=50&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `No court shall take cognizance of an offence under section 42 or section 43 or section 44 except on`
  line `complaint in writing made by the Registrar or any officer authorised by him in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that in relation to clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 42, a court shall take a cognizance`
  line `of an offence on the basis of a certificate issued by the Registrar to the effect that a registered`
  line `geographical indication has been represented as registered in respect of any goods in respect of which it is not in fact registered.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall`
  line `try an offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The offences under section 39 or section 40 or section 41 shall be cognizable.`
  line
  line `(4) Any police officer not below the rank of deputy superintendent of police or equivalent, may, if he`
  line `satisfied that any of the offences referred to in sub-section (3) has been, is being, or is likely to be,`
  line `committed, search and seize without warrant the goods, die, block, machine, plate, other instruments or`
  line `things involved in committing the offence, wherever found, and all the articles so seized shall, as soon as`
  line `practicable, be produced before the Judicial Magistrate of the first class or Metropolitan Magistrate, as the`
  line `case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the police officer, before making any search and seizure, shall obtain the opinion of the`
  line `Registrar on the facts involved in the offence relating to geographical indication and shall abide by the`
  line `opinion so obtained.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person having an interest in any article seized under sub-section (4), may, within fifteen days`
  line `of such seizure, make an application to the Judicial Magistrate of the first class or Metropolitan`
  line `Magistrate, as the case may be, for such article being restored to him and the Magistrate, after hearing the`
  line `application and the prosecution, shall make such order on the application as he may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (2666)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 53
  title `Costs of defence of prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2666&sectionno=51&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `In any prosecution under this Act, the court may order such`
  line `costs to be paid by the accused to the complainant, or by the complainant to the accused, as the court`
  line `deemed reasonable having regard to all the circumstances of the case and the conduct of the parties and`
  line `the costs so awarded shall be recoverable as if they were a fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (2667)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 54
  title `Limitation of prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2667&sectionno=52&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence under this Act shall be commenced`
  line `after the expiration of three years next after the commission of the offence charged or two years after the`
  line `discovery thereof by the prosecutor, whichever expiration first happens.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (2668)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 55
  title `Information as to commission of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2668&sectionno=53&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `An officer of the Government whose duty it is to`
  line `take part in the enforcement of the provisions of this Chapter shall not be compelled in any court to say`
  line `whence he got any information as to the commission of any offence against this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (2669)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 56
  title `Punishment for abetement in India of acts done out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2669&sectionno=54&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `If any person, being within`
  line `India, abets the commission, without India, of any act which, if committed in India, would, under this Act,`
  line `be an offence, he may be tried for such abetement in any place in India in which he may be found, and be`
  line `punished therefor with the punishment to which he would be liable if he had himself committed in that`
  line `place the act which he abetted.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (2670)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 57
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2670&sectionno=55&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against`
  line `any person in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (2671)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 58
  title `Certain persons to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2671&sectionno=56&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Every person appointed under this Act shall be deemed`
  line `to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (2672)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 59
  title `Stay of proceedings where the validity of registration of the geographical indication is questioned etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2672&sectionno=57&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in any suit for infringement of a geographical indication the defendant`
  line `pleads that registration of the geographical indication relating to plaintiff is invalid, the court trying the`
  line `suit (hereinafter referred to as the court), shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if any proceedings for rectification of the register to the geographical indication relating to`
  line `plaintiff or defendant are pending before the Registrar or the ^1[High Court], stay the suit pending`
  line `the final disposal of such proceedings;`
  line
  line `(b) if no such proceedings are pending and the court is satisfied that the plea regarding the`
  line `invalidity of the registration of the geographical indication relating to plaintiff or defendant is prima`
  line `facie tenable, raise an issue regarding the same and adjourn the case for a period of three months from the date of the framing of the issue in order to enable the party concerned to apply to the ^1[High Court] for rectification of the register.`
  line
  line `(2) If the party concerned proves to the court that he has made any such application as is referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) within the time specified therein or within such extended time as the court`
  line `may for sufficient cause allow, the trial of the suit shall stand stayed until the final disposal of the`
  line `rectification proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) If no such application as aforesaid has been made within the time so specified or within such`
  line `extended time as the court may allow, the issue as to the validity of the registration of the geographical`
  line `indication concerned shall be deemed to have been abandoned and the court shall proceed with the suit in`
  line `regard to the other issues in the case.`
  line
  line `(4) The final order made in any rectification proceedings referred to in sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be binding upon the parties and the court shall dispose of the suit conformably to`
  line `such order in so far as it relates to the issue as to the validity of the registration of the geographical`
  line indication.
  line
  line `(5) The stay of a suit for the infringement of a geographical indication under this section shall not`
  line `preclude the court from making any interlocutory order (including any order granting an injunction,`
  line `directing account to be kept, appointing a receiver or attaching any property), during the period of the stay`
  line `of the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (2673)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 60
  title `Application for rectification of register to be made to High Court in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2673&sectionno=58&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in a suit for infringement of a registered geographical indication the validity of the`
  line `registration of the geographical indication relating to plaintiff is questioned by the defendant or where in`
  line `any such suit the plaintiff questions the validity of the registration of the geographical indication relating`
  line `to defendant, the issue as to the validity of the registration of the geographical indication concerned shall`
  line `be determined only on an application for the rectification of the register and, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 27, such application shall be made to the ^1[High Court] and not to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), where an application for rectification of the register is`
  line `made to the Registrar under section 27, the Registrar may, if he thinks fit, refer the application at any`
  line `stage of the proceedings to the ^1[High Court].`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (2674)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 61
  title `Implied warranty on sale of indicated goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2674&sectionno=59&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Where a geographical indication has been`
  line `applied to the goods on sale or in the contract for sale of any goods, the seller shall be deemed to warrant`
  line `that the geographical indication is a genuine geographical indication and not falsely applied, unless the`
  line `contrary is expressed in writing signed by or on behalf of the seller and delivered at the time of the sale of`
  line `goods on contract to and accepted by the buyer.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (2675)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 62
  title `Powers of Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2675&sectionno=60&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `In all proceedings under this Act before the Registrar,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Registrar shall have all the powers of a civil court for the purposes of receiving evidence,`
  line `administering oaths, enforcing the attendance of witnesses, compelling the discovery and production`
  line `of documents and issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) the Registrar may, subject to any rules made in this behalf under section 87, make such orders`
  line `as to costs as he considers reasonable, and any such order shall be executable as a decree of a civil`
  line court;
  line
  line `(c) the Registrar may, on an application made in the prescribed manner, review his own decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (2676)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 63
  title `Exercise of discretionary power by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2676&sectionno=61&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 64, the`
  line `Registrar shall not exercise any discretionary or other power vested in him by this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder adversely to a person applying for the exercise of that power without (if so required by that`
  line `person within the prescribed time) giving to the person an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (2677)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 64
  title `Evidence before Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2677&sectionno=62&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act before the Registrar, evidence`
  line `shall be given by affidavit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar may, if he thinks fit, take oral evidence in lieu of, or in addition to, such`
  line `evidence by affidavit`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (2678)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 65
  title `Death of party to a proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1.The words “the Appellate Board or” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2678&sectionno=63&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `If a person who is a party to a proceeding under this Act (not`
  line `being a proceeding before ^1*** a court) dies pending the proceeding, the Registrar may,`
  line `on request, and on proof to his satisfaction of the transmission of the interest of the deceased person,`
  line `substitute in the proceeding his successor in interest in his place, or, if the Registrar is of opinion that the`
  line `interest of the deceased person is sufficiently represented by the surviving parties, permit the proceeding`
  line `to continue without the substitution of his successor in interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (2679)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 66
  title `Extension of time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2679&sectionno=64&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Registrar is satisfied, on application made to him in the prescribed`
  line `manner and accompanied by the prescribed fee, that there is sufficient cause for extending the time for`
  line `doing any act (not being a time expressly provided in the Act), whether the time so specified has expired`
  line `or not, he may, subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose, extend the time and inform the`
  line `parties accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to require the Registrar to hear the parties before`
  line `disposing of an application for extension of time, and no appeal shall lie from any order of the Registrar`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (2680)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 67
  title Abandonment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2680&sectionno=65&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Where, in the opinion of the Registrar, an applicant is in default in the`
  line `prosecution of an application filed under this Act, the Registrar may, by notice require the applicant to`
  line `remedy the default within a time specified and after giving him, if so, desired, an opportunity of being`
  line `heard, treat the application as abandoned, unless the default is remedied within the time specified in the`
  line notice.
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (2681)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 68
  title `Suit for infringement, etc., to be instituted before district court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2681&sectionno=66&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the infringement of a registered geographical indication; or`
  line
  line `(b) relating to any right in a registered geographical indication; or`
  line
  line `(c) for passing of arising out of the use by the defendant of any geographical indication which is`
  line `indentical on with or deceptively similar to the geographical indication relating to the plaintiff,`
  line `whether registered or unregistered,`
  line
  line `shall be instituted in any court inferior to a district court having jurisdiction to try the suit.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1), a "district court having jurisdiction"`
  line `shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, include a district court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction, at the`
  line `time of the institution of the suit or other proceeding, the person instituting the suit or proceeding, or,`
  line `where there are more than one such persons any of them, actually and voluntarily resides or carries on`
  line `business or personally works for gain.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-section (2), "person" includes the registered proprietor and`
  line `the authorised user.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (2682)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 69
  title `Relief in suit for infringement or for passing off.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2682&sectionno=67&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The relief which a court may grant in`
  line `any suit for infringement or for passing off referred to in section 66 includes injunction (subject to such`
  line `terms, if any, as the court thinks fit) and at the option of the plaintiff, either damages or account of profits,`
  line `together with or without any order for the delivery-up of the infringing labels and indications for`
  line `destruction or erasure.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of injunction under sub-section (1) may include an ex parte injunction or any`
  line `interlocutory order for any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for discovery of documents;`
  line
  line `(b) preserving of infringing goods, documents or other evidence which are related to the`
  line `subject-matter of the suit;`
  line
  line `(c) restraining the defendant from disposing of or dealing with his assets in a manner which may`
  line `adversely affect plaintiffs ability to recover damages, costs or other pecuniary remedies which may`
  line `be finally awarded to the plaintiff.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the court shall not grant relief by way of`
  line `damages (other than nominal damages) on account of profits in any case--`
  line
  line `(a) where in a suit for infringement the defendant satisfies the court--`
  line
  line `(i) that at the time he commenced to use the geographical indication complained of in the suit`
  line `he was unaware and had no reasonable ground for believing that the geographical indication of`
  line `the plaintiff was on the register; and`
  line
  line `(ii) that when he became aware of the existence and nature of the plaintiffs right in the`
  line `geographical indication, he forthwith ceased to use the geographical indication in relation to good`
  line `in respect of which it was registered; or`
  line
  line `(b) where in a suit for passing off, the defendant satisfies the court--`
  line
  line `(i) that at the time he commenced to use the geographical indication complained of in the suit`
  line `he was unaware and had no reasonable ground for believing that the geographical indication`
  line `relating to the plaintiff was in use; and`
  line
  line `(ii) that when he became aware of the existence and nature of the geographical indication`
  line `relating to the plaintiff he forthwith ceased to use the geographical indication complained of.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (2683)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 70
  title `Authorised user to be impleaded in certain proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2683&sectionno=68&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every proceeding under`
  line `Chapter VI or under section 31, every authorised user of a geographical indication to which such`
  line `proceeding relate, who is not himself an applicant in respect of any proceeding under that Chapter or`
  line `section, shall be made a party to the proceeding.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, an authorised user so made a party to the`
  line `proceeding shall not be liable for any costs unless he enters an appearance and takes part in the`
  line proceeding.
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (2684)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 71
  title `Evidence of entries in register, etc., and things done by the Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2684&sectionno=69&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of any`
  line `entry in the register or of any document referred to in sub-section (1) of section 78 purporting to be`
  line `certified by the Registrar and sealed with the seal of the Geographical Indications Registry shall be`
  line `admitted in evidence in all courts and in all proceedings without further proof or production of the`
  line original.
  line
  line `(2) A certificate purporting to be under the hand of the Registrar as to any entry, matter or thing that`
  line `he is authorised by this Act or the rules to make or do shall be prima facie evidence of the entry having`
  line `been made, and of the contents thereof, or of the matter or things having been done or not done.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (2685)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 72
  title `Registrar and other officers not compellable to produce register, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2685&sectionno=70&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar or any`
  line `officer of the Geographical Indications Registry shall not, in any legal proceedings to which he is not a`
  line `party, be compellable to produce the register or any other document in his custody, the contents of which`
  line `can be proved by the production of a certified copy issued under this Act or to appear as a witness to`
  line `prove the matters therein recorded unless by order of the court made for special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (2686)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power to require goods to show indication of origin.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2686&sectionno=71&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, require that goods of any class specified in the notification which are`
  line `made or produced beyond the limits of India and imported into India, or, which are made or produced`
  line `within the limits of India, shall, from such date as may be appointed by the notification not being less than`
  line `three months from its issue, have applied to them an indication of the country or place in which they were`
  line `made or produced, or of the name and address of the manufacturer or the person for whom the goods were`
  line manufactured.
  line
  line `(2) The notification may specify the manner in which such indication shall be applied, that is to say,`
  line `whether to goods themselves or in any other manner, and the times or occasions on which the presence of`
  line `the indication shall be necessary, that is to say, whether on importation only, or also at the time of sale,`
  line `whether by wholesale or retail or both.`
  line
  line `(3) No notification under this section shall be issued, unless application is made for its issue by`
  line `persons or associations substantially representing the interests of dealers in, or manufacturers, producers, or users of, the goods concerned, or unless the Central Government is otherwise convinced that it is`
  line `necessary in the public interest to issue the notification, with or without such inquiry, as the Central`
  line `Government may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of section 23 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) shall apply to the issue`
  line `of a notification under this section as they apply to the making of a rule or bye-law the making of which is`
  line `subject to the condition of previous publication.`
  line
  line `(5) A notification under this section shall not apply to goods made or produced beyond the limits of`
  line `India and imported into India, if in respect of those goods, the Commissioner of Customs is satisfied at the`
  line `time of importation that they are intended for exportation whether after transhipment in or transit through`
  line `India or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (2687)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 74
  title `Certificate of validity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22, for "Appellate Board" (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2687&sectionno=72&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `If in any legal proceedings for rectification of the register before the`
  line `^1[High Court] a decision is on contest given in favour of the registered proprietor or, as the case may`
  line `be, authorised user of the geographical indication on the issue as to the validity of the registration of the`
  line `geographical indication or the authorised user, the ^1[High Court] may grant a certificate to that effect,`
  line `and if such a certificate is granted, then, in any subsequent legal proceeding in which the said validity`
  line `comes into question the said proprietor or the authorised user, as the case may be, on obtaining a final`
  line `order or judgment in his favour affirming validity of the registration of the geographical indication or the`
  line `authorised user, as the case may be, shall unless the said final order or judgment for sufficient reason`
  line `directs otherwise, be entitled to his full cost charges and expenses as between legal practitioner and client.`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (2688)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 75
  title `Groundless threats of legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2688&sectionno=73&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person, by means of circulars,`
  line `advertisements or otherwise, threatens a person with an action or proceeding for infringement of a`
  line `geographical indication which is registered, or alleged by the first-mentioned person to be registered, or`
  line `with some other like proceeding, a person aggrieved may, whether the person making the threats is or is`
  line `not the registered proprietor or the authorised user of the geographical indication, bring a suit against the`
  line `first-mentioned person and may obtain a declaration to the effect that the threats are unjustifiable, and an`
  line `injunction against the continuance of the threats and may recover such damages (if any) as he has`
  line `sustained, unless the first-mentioned person satisfies the court that the geographical indication is`
  line `registered and that the acts in respect of which the proceedings were threatened, constitute, or, if done,`
  line `would constitute, an infringement of the geographical indication.`
  line
  line `(2) The last preceding sub-section does not apply if the registered proprietor of the geographical`
  line `indication or an authorised user thereof with due diligence commences and prosecutes an action against`
  line `the person threatened for infringement of the geographical indication.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall render a legal practitioner or a registered geographical indications`
  line `agent liable to an action under this section in respect of an act done by him in his professional capacity on`
  line `behalf of a client.`
  line
  line `(4) A suit under sub-section (1) shall not be instituted in any court inferior to a district court.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (2689)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 76
  title `Address for service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2689&sectionno=74&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `An address for service stated in an application or notice of opposition`
  line `shall, for the purposes of the application or notice of opposition be deemed to be the address of the`
  line `applicant or opponent, as the case may be, and all documents in relation to the application or notice of`
  line `opposition may be served by leaving them at or sending them by post to the address for service of the`
  line `applicant or opponent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (2690)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 77
  title `Trade usages, etc., to be taken into consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22, for tribunal (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2690&sectionno=75&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding relating to a`
  line `geographical indication, the ^1[Registrar or the High Court, as the case may be,] shall admit evidence of the usages of the trade concerned and of any`
  line `relevant geographical indication legitimately used by other persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (2691)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 78
  title Agents.
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2691&sectionno=76&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `Where, by or under this Act, any act, other than the making of an affidavit, is required`
  line `to be done before the Registrar by any person, the act may, subject to the rules made in this behalf, be`
  line `done instead of by that person himself, by a person duly authorised in the prescribed manner, who is,--`
  line
  line `(a) a legal practitioner, or`
  line
  line `(b) a person registered in the prescribed manner as a geographical indications agent, or`
  line
  line `(c) a person in the sole and regular employment of the principal.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (2692)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 79
  title Indexes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2692&sectionno=77&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `There shall be kept under the directions and supervision of the Registrar,--`
  line
  line `(a) an index of registered geographical indications,`
  line
  line `(b) an index of geographical indications in respect of which applications for registration are`
  line pending,
  line
  line `(c) an index of the names of the proprietors of registered geographical indications, and`
  line
  line `(d) an index of the names of authorised users.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (2693)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 80
  title `Documents open to public inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2693&sectionno=78&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following documents, subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed, be open to public inspection at the Geographical Indications Registry,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the register and any document upon which any entry in the register is based;`
  line
  line `(b) every notice of opposition to the registration of a geographical indication, application for`
  line `rectification before the Registrar, counter-statement thereto, and any affidavit or document filed by`
  line `the parties in any proceedings before the Registrar;`
  line
  line `(c) the indexes mentioned in section 77; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other documents as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such register is maintained wholly or partly on computer, the inspection of`
  line `such register under this section shall be made by inspecting the computer print out of the relevant`
  line `entry in the register so maintained on computer.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person may, on an application to the Registrar and on payment of such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed, obtain a certified copy of any entry in the register or any document referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (2694)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 81
  title `Reports of Registrar to be placed before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2694&sectionno=79&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause to`
  line `be placed before both Houses of Parliament once a year a report respecting the execution by or under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (2695)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 82
  title `Fees and surcharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2695&sectionno=80&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be paid in respect of applications and registrations and`
  line `other matters under this Act such fees and surcharge as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a fee is payable in respect of the doing of an act by the Registrar, the Registrar shall not do`
  line `that act until the fee has been paid.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a fee is payable in respect of the filing of a document at the Geographical Indications`
  line `Registry, the document shall be deemed not to have been filed at the registry until the fee has been paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (2696)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 83
  title `Savings in respect of certain matters in Chapter VIII.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2696&sectionno=81&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in Chapter VIII shall--`
  line
  line `(a) exempt any person from any suit or other proceeding which might, but for anything in that`
  line `Chapter, be brought against him, or`
  line
  line `(b) be construed so as to render liable to any prosecution or punishment any servant of a master`
  line `resident in India who in good faith acts in obedience to the instructions of such master, and, on`
  line `demand made by or on behalf of the prosecutor, has given full information as to his master and as to`
  line `the instructions which he has received from his master.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (2697)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 84
  title `Declaration as to title of geographical indication not registrable under the Registration Act, 1908.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2697&sectionno=82&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), no`
  line `document declaring or purporting to declare any title of a person to a geographical indication other than a`
  line `registered geographical indication shall be registered under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (2698)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 85
  title `Government to be bound.`
  content `The provisions of this Act shall be binding on the Government.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2698&sectionno=83&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (2699)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 86
  title `Special provisions relating to applications for registration from citizens of convention countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2699&sectionno=84&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to the fulfilment of a treaty, convention or arrangement with any country or`
  line `a country which is a member of a group of countries or union of countries or Inter-Governmental`
  line `Organisations outside India which affords to citizens of India similar privileges as granted to its own`
  line `citizens, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare such country or`
  line `group of countries or union of countries or Inter-Governmental Organisations to be a convention country`
  line `or convention countries for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this Act or the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of 1999) shall prevent a continued`
  line `and similar use of geographical indication relating to a country or a country which is a member of a group`
  line `of countries or union of countries or any Inter-Governmental Organisations, as the case may be, notified`
  line `under sub-section (1) identifying wines or spirits in connection with goods by any citizen or domiciliary`
  line `of such country who has used that geographical indication in continuous manner with regard to such`
  line `goods or any goods relating to such goods, as the case may be, in any part of the territory of that country`
  line either--
  line
  line `(a) for at least ten years preceding the 15th day of April, 1994; or`
  line
  line `(b) in good faith preceding the date referred to in clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (2700)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 87
  title `Provision as to reciprocity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2700&sectionno=85&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Where any country or a country which is a member of a group of`
  line `countries or union of countries or any Inter-Governmental Organisation specified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette does not accord to citizens of India the`
  line `same rights in respect of the registration and protection of geographical indications as it accords to its own`
  line `nationals, no nationals of such country or a country which is a member of a group of countries or union or`
  line `countries or Inter-Governmental Organisations, as the case may be, shall be entitled--`
  line
  line `(a) to apply for the registration of, or be registered as the proprietor of geographical indication;`
  line
  line `(b) to apply for registration or be registered as an authorised user of a geographical indication.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (2701)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 88
  title `Powers of Central Government to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2701&sectionno=86&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving`
  line `effect to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be`
  line `necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of five years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (2702)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766&sectionId=2702&sectionno=87&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_60_00002_199948_1517807322766
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the matters to be included in the Register of Geographical Indications under sub-section (1),`
  line `and the safeguards to be observed in the maintenance of such register in computer floppies or`
  line `diskettes under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of incorporation of particulars relating to registration of geographical indications`
  line `in Part A under sub-section (2) and the manner of incorporation of particulars relating to the`
  line `registration of the authorised users under sub-section (3) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the classification of goods and the manner of publication of the alphabetical index of`
  line `classification of goods and the definite territory or locality or region for the purpose of registration of`
  line `geographical indications under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which and the manner in which an application for registration of a geographical`
  line `indication may be made and the fees which may accompany the application under sub-section (1) and`
  line `the particulars to be made in the statement of producers of goods who proposes to be initially`
  line `registered with the registration under clause (f) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of publication of advertisement of accepted application, for registration of`
  line `geographical indications, etc., under sub-section (1), and the manner of notifying the corrections or`
  line `amendments made in the application under sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which and the fee which may accompany an application and the manner of`
  line `giving notice under sub-section (1) and the manner of sending counter statement under sub-section (2)`
  line `and the manner of submission of evidence and the time therefor under sub-section (4) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(g) the form of certificate of registration under sub-section (2) and the manner of giving notice to`
  line `the applicant under sub-section (3) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of applying for registration as an authorised user under sub-section (1) and the`
  line `manner of submitting statements and documents along with such application and the fee which may`
  line `accompany such application under sub-section (2) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of making application, the time within which such application is to be made and`
  line `the fee payable with each application, under sub-section (3) and the time within which the Registrar`
  line `shall send notice and the manner of such notice under sub-section (4) and the form in which and the`
  line `fee which may accompany an application for renewal to be made under sub-section (5) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of making applications under sub-sections (1) and (2), the manner of giving notice`
  line `under sub-section (4) and the manner of service of notice of rectification under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of making an application for correction, etc., under section 28;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of making an application under sub-section (1), the manner of advertising an`
  line `application under sub-section (1), the time and manner of notice by which an application may be`
  line `opposed under sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of advertisement under sub-section (2) of section 30;`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(o) the form in which an application for rectification shall be made, under sub-section (1)of`
  line `section 34;`
  line
  line `^2[(oa) the manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty under section 37A;`
  line
  line `(ob) the form and manner of preferring appeal under sub-section (2) of section 37B;]`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of making an application for review under clause (c) of section 60;`
  line
  line `(q) the time within which an application is to be made to the Registrar for exercising his`
  line `discretionary power under section 61;`
  line
  line `(r) the manner of making an application and the fee payable therefore under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 64;`
  line
  line `(s) the manner of authorising any person to act and the manner of registration of a geographical indications agent under section 76;`
  line
  line `(t) the fee and surcharge payable for applications and registrations and other matters under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 80;`
  line
  line `(u) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Clause (n) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 22 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
